wiki.content: "Automático" (stylized in capital letters) is a song performed by the Argentine singer María Becerra, written by her and produced by Nico Cotton. It was released on September 8, 2022 through 300 Entertainment, as the second single from her second studio album, La nena de Argentina. The reggaeton song, fused with dembow rhythms with a hint of synth pop, is inspired by the pioneers of the genre, such as Daddy Yankee. It was composed by the same artist and the production was in charge of Nico Cotton. According to Becerra, the melody of the song was created by herself and was born, after leaving the supermarket towards the parking lot, where she composed the chorus. Regarding the composition process, she mentioned to Billboard magazine that for the She herself was inspired by the pioneers of reggaeton to give life to this melody. And in turn, through a press release, she declared that she wanted to give it the modern touch that marks her own style, with the sensuality and strong personality that characterizes her. The videoclip, directed by Julián Levy, was published simultaneously with the song and takes place in a car workshop location and its theme is focused on the adrenaline of speed.3 It had a positive reception due to its artistic style and, to In turn, it was compared for its style to Fast & Furious.
